selling ties on the street.

02:51.472 --> 02:53.841
Ugly ties.

02:53.841 --> 02:55.476
And I think they're hot.

02:55.476 --> 02:57.411
They're not hot,
just inexpensive.

02:57.411 --> 02:59.613
Well, Why'd you bring him to me?
I don't wear ties.

02:59.613 --> 03:02.116
Well, it's all here right here
on the school card.

03:02.116 --> 03:04.183
We couldn't locate his mother.

03:04.184 --> 03:05.952
His father's deceased.

03:05.953 --> 03:08.989
And the school card listed you
as the next closest relative.

03:08.989 --> 03:10.557
Now, let me get this straight.
You got a badge.

03:10.557 --> 03:11.858
You got a kid selling ties.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.260
Have you got a charge?

03:13.260 --> 03:14.428
I'm a truant officer.

03:14.428 --> 03:15.661
He's playing hooky.

03:15.662 --> 03:16.830
Second time this week.

03:16.830 --> 03:18.098
-(snaps fingers)
- Get over here.

03:18.098 --> 03:19.366
