Fonz!

03:58.939 --> 04:01.408
Hey, Fonz!

04:01.408 --> 04:03.399
I got to tell you something.

04:04.812 --> 04:06.078
You should've been

04:06.079 --> 04:07.847
at the girl's
volleyball game today, Fonz.

04:07.848 --> 04:09.416
One of the girls forgot
to wear her...

04:09.416 --> 04:12.352
- Richie, this is not...
- And...

04:12.352 --> 04:14.688
Chachi. Cut school.

04:14.688 --> 04:16.923
Truant officer. Tell him.

04:16.923 --> 04:18.156
Isn't he a little young to hear

04:18.158 --> 04:19.892
about a girl
who forgot to wear her...

04:19.892 --> 04:21.194
Not about a girl.

04:21.195 --> 04:23.130
About school.

04:23.130 --> 04:24.498
- Oh!
- Tell him.

04:24.498 --> 04:26.433
Oh, cut school?

04:26.433 --> 04:28.702
Oh, Chachi, you ought to know
better than that.

04:28.702 --> 04:30.204
You just can't go around
cutting school.

04:30.204 --> 04:32.104
- That's just not a nice...
- Uh, Cunningham, you don't have

04:32.105 --> 04:34.341
to be polite;
he is a family disgrace.

04:34.341 --> 04:35.642
You should be in school.

04:35.642 --> 04:36.776
Tell him!

04:36.777 --> 04:38.377
But I don't do good in school.

04:38.378 --> 04:39.913
I hate it! It's boring!

04:39.913 --> 04:41.715
I mean, who cares
about the Civil War?

04:41.715 --> 04:43.046
We won.

04:45.252 --> 04:47.621
Well, um, maybe
if you were doing better,

04:47.621 --> 04:48.722
y-you'd like it more.

04:48.722 --> 04:49.923
Aw, come on.

04:49.923 --> 04:52.192
The only subject
I'm not behind in is lunch.

04:52.192 --> 04:53.894
A-All right, all right, okay.

04:53.894 --> 04:55.462
How about...
how about getting a tutor?

04:55.462 --> 04:57.397
Cunningham,
we're talking school here,

04:57.397 --> 04:59.332
not playing horns.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.767
Oh, Fonz, remember when I...
when I helped you with school?

05:01.768 --> 05:04.904
That's all a tutor is,
just a private instructor.

05:04.905 --> 05:07.674
I knew that.

05:07.674 --> 05:09.743
I just wanted you
to explain it to him.

05:09.743 --> 05:10.944
How about that, huh?

05:10.944 --> 05:12.343
Cunningham's gonna toot you.

05:13.547 --> 05:15.082
Oh, me?

05:15.082 --> 05:16.315
Fonz...

05:16.316 --> 05:17.884
Well, you see,
I'm-I'm in college now.

05:17.885 --> 05:19.518
I got a lot of reading to do,

05:19.519 --> 05:22.288
and, you know,
term papers, and...

05:22.289 --> 05:23.789
I've been seeing Laurie Beth.

05:23.790 --> 05:25.425
You know, the cheerleader?

05:25.425 --> 05:26.693
And you know how it is.

05:26.693 --> 05:28.058
- Sis-boom-bah!
- Yeah.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.231
I totally understand, you know?

05:31.231 --> 05:33.200
Those sis-boom-bahs
can tire you right out.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.402
- Yeah.
- Especially those boom-bahs.

05:35.402 --> 05:37.104
CHACHI:
I don't want a tutor anyway.

05:37.104 --> 05:38.572
Forget school.

05:38.572 --> 05:40.439
I'm making 35 bucks a week.

05:40.440 --> 05:42.242
Chicken feed.

05:42.242 --> 05:44.444
Well, it's more than those nerds
at school make.

05:44.444 --> 05:45.679
No. no. no, no.

05:45.679 --> 05:48.215
Uh, statistics show
that high school graduates

05:48.215 --> 05:50.484
earn more per capita
than high school dropouts.

05:50.484 --> 05:52.286
And then if you become
a college graduate,

05:52.286 --> 05:53.420
why, the difference is
just drastically...

05:53.420 --> 05:55.289
Uh, Cunningham,
Cunningham, Cunningham?

05:55.289 --> 05:57.990
You see how smart
school can make you?

05:57.991 --> 06:01.228
Just make it more interesting
next time, will you?

06:01.228 --> 06:03.063
Yeah, but school's a drag.

06:03.063 --> 06:04.998
Hey, let me tell you something.
You trust me.

06:04.998 --> 06:06.766
School is cool.

06:06.767 --> 06:07.668
If you say so.

06:07.668 --> 06:09.303
I say so.

06:09.303 --> 06:11.570
Now, what are we gonna do
about this tutoring jazz?

06:11.571 --> 06:13.706
Well, what about Joanie?

06:13.707 --> 06:14.975
- I think it might be good.
- Huh?

06:14.975 --> 06:17.945
Because she's closer
to his grade anyway.

06:17.945 --> 06:19.980
I'm liking it better already.

06:19.980 --> 06:21.081
(chuckles)

06:21.081 --> 06:23.784
Me and Blue Eyes? Wah-wah-wah.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.452
