Parents!

12:45.532 --> 12:48.001
<i>I'm going to Jenny Pint-Mo's
to see the sf ides</i>

12:48.001 --> 12:50.637
of her vacation at Sunny Slopes.

12:50.637 --> 12:53.540
Sunny Slopes?
That's a nudist colony!

12:53.540 --> 12:54.973
Joanie!

12:54.974 --> 12:56.576
Feel better, Dad?
(chuckles)

12:56.576 --> 12:59.479
Howard, here.

12:59.479 --> 13:02.615
Hey, evening, Cunningham family.

13:02.615 --> 13:05.318
Look, I just found your paper
on my doorstep again.

13:05.318 --> 13:07.287
Your newsboy's got a great arm.

13:07.287 --> 13:09.389
Why aren't you talking?

13:09.389 --> 13:11.157
I thought I did.

13:11.157 --> 13:12.792
- To Chachi.
- No!

13:12.792 --> 13:14.527
Oh, now you're angry.
I understand.

13:14.527 --> 13:16.062
I'm not angry.

13:16.062 --> 13:20.166
I don't talk to short people
that tell me to get lost.

13:20.166 --> 13:22.435
Fonzie, Chachi has a problem.

13:22.435 --> 13:23.703
Now, you can't ignore him.

13:23.703 --> 13:26.005
Look, Mr. C,
I gave that boy a plan,

13:26.005 --> 13:27.607
he threw it back in my face.

13:27.607 --> 13:28.842
He's on his own.

13:28.842 --> 13:30.477
He's just a little boy!

13:30.477 --> 13:34.346
Well, so was I when I got caught
on the swings in kindergarten.

13:34.347 --> 13:36.049
The teacher said,
"You got yourself up there,

13:36.049 --> 13:38.381
you get yourself down."

13:40.353 --> 13:41.554
So what'd you do then?

13:41.554 --> 13:43.215
I climbed down,
I chased her up there!

13:46.693 --> 13:49.629
Well, good for you.

13:49.629 --> 13:52.198
Marion, that is not
the problem here.

13:52.198 --> 13:54.767
You're absolutely right.
You're absolutely right, Mr. C.

13:54.768 --> 13:56.703
It's not the problem.
It's Chachi's.

13:56.703 --> 13:58.505
It's up to him.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.507
Boy, just like a parent.

14:00.507 --> 14:03.208
I'm not the kid's parent, Red.

14:03.209 --> 14:04.644
Fonzie...

14:04.644 --> 14:07.280
Stay with me, will you, Marion?

14:07.280 --> 14:09.783
Now, look, the boy
doesn't have a father.

14:09.783 --> 14:13.583
He needs someone he can
look up to, a-a male figure.

14:17.757 --> 14:20.093
He does look up to you
like a father, Fonz.

14:20.093 --> 14:22.594
A lot of people do.

14:22.595 --> 14:24.530
Do you have any idea
how many times

14:24.531 --> 14:26.466
I tried to tell him
to get lost?

14:26.466 --> 14:27.734
You did?

14:27.734 --> 14:30.335
Well, not in so many words.

14:30.336 --> 14:33.406
But, see, the important thing
is that he never did.

14:33.406 --> 14:35.575
I always knew he'd be there.

14:35.575 --> 14:37.744
FONZIE:
The subject is close-amundo!

14:37.744 --> 14:42.682
Now, look, I really appreciate
what you're all trying to do,

14:42.682 --> 14:45.218
but there's the Fonzarelli code
that says,

14:45.218 --> 14:49.355
"if someone slams a door
in your face..." Huh?

14:49.355 --> 14:50.690
"...you don't ring the doorbell

14:50.690 --> 14:53.455
so they can slam it back
in your face again!" Whoa!

14:55.495 --> 14:58.598
Well, he certainly made
his position very clear.

14:58.598 --> 15:02.569
Oh, Howard, what am I gonna
do with this?

15:02.569 --> 15:04.469
Knit on it, Marion.

15:12.812 --> 15:14.147
(slurping)

15:14.147 --> 15:15.842
<i>II</i>

15:17.183 --> 15:19.585
- Hi, Al.
- Hi, Rich.

15:19.586 --> 15:21.855
How many has he had?

15:21.855 --> 15:24.257
He's been here
since this morning.

15:24.257 --> 15:26.726
Hey, Al, hurry up
with my drink.

15:26.726 --> 15:28.995
Oh, and bring one
for my friend here.

15:28.995 --> 15:31.760
See that? Try to talk some sense
into him, will you?

15:35.869 --> 15:39.204
Chachi.

15:39.205 --> 15:40.440
Look, I-l know you're...

15:40.440 --> 15:43.408
you're busted up
over this Fonzie thing, but...

15:43.409 --> 15:44.644
What Fonzie thing?

15:44.644 --> 15:46.713
There's this chick,
you know what I mean?

15:46.713 --> 15:48.413
Oh, it's-it's a girl, huh?

15:48.414 --> 15:50.249
<i>Yeah, Boom Boom Lame.</i>

15:50.250 --> 15:51.618
Huh, Boom Boom.

15:51.618 --> 15:53.353
She dumped you?

15:53.353 --> 15:56.656
Yeah, yeah.
She ran off with a TV star.

15:56.656 --> 15:58.691
I think it was Snooky Lanson.

15:58.691 --> 15:59.892
I'll get over it.

15:59.893 --> 16:01.426
Yeah.

16:01.427 --> 16:04.697
Well, uh...
you want to tell me about it?

16:04.697 --> 16:06.365
Hey, listen, Cunningham,

16:06.366 --> 16:08.535
don't try any of this
child psychologyjunk on me.

16:08.535 --> 16:11.204
All right, all right,
you're right.

16:11.204 --> 16:14.841
We don't need those games...
do we, pal?

16:14.841 --> 16:17.377
Think I'm dumb enough
for that old buddy routine?

16:17.377 --> 16:20.046
Ha.

16:20.046 --> 16:21.714
Routine?!

16:21.714 --> 16:23.549
Let me tell you something,
squirt!

16:23.550 --> 16:26.251
I've had enough of this stuff!
And let me tell you...!

16:26.252 --> 16:28.454
And don't try
the anger bit, either.

16:28.454 --> 16:29.944
I'm hip to that one, too.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.163
All right.

16:37.163 --> 16:39.732
All right,
I got one last routine left.

16:39.732 --> 16:42.101
- Oh, yeah? What's that? -Yeah,
it's a totally new approach.

16:42.101 --> 16:43.102
What's that?

16:43.102 --> 16:45.404
Truth, honesty.

16:45.405 --> 16:46.905
That's a new one.

16:46.906 --> 16:50.276
Well, it's not new,
but it's the best.

16:50.276 --> 16:53.880
Look, I know it's tough
getting kicked out of school.

16:53.880 --> 16:55.648
School isn't important.

16:55.648 --> 16:57.617
Mr. Super Cool dropped out.

16:57.617 --> 16:59.052
Oh, true, true.

16:59.052 --> 17:00.453
But Fonzie
was cool enough to know

17:00.453 --> 17:02.021
that he wanted to go back
and finish later.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.923
- And you know why?
- Because he wanted to.

17:03.923 --> 17:05.258
Well, that's what
he tells everybody,

17:05.258 --> 17:06.526
but that's not the real reason.

17:06.526 --> 17:08.560
- It isn't?
- No.

17:08.560 --> 17:10.363
No, it was pride.

17:10.363 --> 17:11.998
Fonzie couldn't stand
being a quitter.

17:11.998 --> 17:13.433
He had to prove something.

17:13.433 --> 17:16.102
He had to prove that he could
finish anything that he started.

17:16.102 --> 17:17.270
I can do that.

17:17.270 --> 17:19.705
- Sure you can.
- But I don't want to.

17:19.705 --> 17:21.907
I mean, I'm not gonna go
crawling back

17:21.907 --> 17:23.309
and apologize
to some principal.

17:23.309 --> 17:25.111
- Well, you don't have to crawl.
- Forget it!

17:25.111 --> 17:27.180
It's the code.

17:27.180 --> 17:30.844
Fonzie says, "You made
your bed bad, you get wrinkled."

17:33.353 --> 17:36.489
All right,
keep your stupid codes,

17:36.489 --> 17:38.424
because I've had it.

17:38.424 --> 17:40.059
Hey, Richie, wait.

17:40.059 --> 17:42.595
♪ First star I see ♪

17:42.595 --> 17:46.332
♪ Won't you bring
my baby to me... ♪

17:46.332 --> 17:48.467
What do I do?

17:48.468 --> 17:49.936
All right.

17:49.936 --> 17:52.472
Well, you're a...
you're a salesman, aren't you?

17:52.472 --> 17:53.740
The best.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.041
All right, all right.

17:55.041 --> 17:58.311
You go find that principal,
and you sell yourself.

17:58.311 --> 18:01.114
Hey, yeah.

18:01.114 --> 18:03.281
If I can sell those stupid ties,

18:03.282 --> 18:06.018
why can't I sell
a terrific product-- me?

18:06.019 --> 18:08.755
That's right.
Okay, in the meantime,

18:08.755 --> 18:10.989
I'll go talk to Fonzie, see what
I can do about your job.

18:10.990 --> 18:12.291
Is that fair enough?

18:12.291 --> 18:13.793
Fair enough.

18:13.793 --> 18:15.662
Oh, and, uh, I'll tell you
what I'll do, Cunningham.

18:15.662 --> 18:17.130
I'll even take back
your old man's tie.

18:17.130 --> 18:19.364
(chuckles) Well, you don't have
to go that far.

18:19.365 --> 18:22.201
Oh, uh, no, thanks, Al.
I don't need it now.

18:22.201 --> 18:24.203
See you, Rich. Thanks.

18:24.203 --> 18:25.568
See you, Chach.

18:27.306 --> 18:29.297
Oh, boy. (chuckles)

18:32.412 --> 18:34.846
So, he thinks
he's got problems, huh?

18:34.847 --> 18:36.015
Yeah.

18:36.015 --> 18:38.217
Ever tell you
about Rosa Coletti?

18:38.217 --> 18:40.019
Yeah.

18:40.019 --> 18:42.488
I first met Rosa in '34.

18:42.488 --> 18:45.157
No, no, it was 1935.

18:45.158 --> 18:47.827
She was a tiny girl.

18:47.827 --> 18:50.125
Shiny black hair...

18:51.564 --> 18:53.054
(engine revving)

18:56.436 --> 18:57.801
Fonz?

18:58.838 --> 19:00.907
Fonz?!

19:00.907 --> 19:03.274
Fonz, would you cut the noise?!

19:05.611 --> 19:08.314
Noise?

19:08.314 --> 19:10.449
You calling this noise?

19:10.450 --> 19:12.517
This symphony of pistons?

19:12.518 --> 19:15.955
(hums Beethoven's
No. <i>5</i> Symphony)

19:15.955 --> 19:18.024
No, it's-it's real nice, Fonz.

19:18.024 --> 19:20.126
Look, I-l got somebody
waiting outside,

19:20.126 --> 19:23.663
and, uh, well, he'd like to try
and get a job here.

19:23.663 --> 19:26.699
Hey, I don't need any help.
You think Beethoven needed help?

19:26.699 --> 19:29.068
Well, maybe I could just
bring him in,

19:29.068 --> 19:31.604
and-and you could give him
an interview or something, okay?

19:31.604 --> 19:34.040
What's his name, Cunningham?

19:34.040 --> 19:36.374
Charles Arcola.

19:36.375 --> 19:38.210
Chachi?

19:38.211 --> 19:43.249
In your own words, Richard,
"Ha-ha-ha."

19:43.249 --> 19:44.851
It didn't work.
I've got no openings.

19:44.851 --> 19:46.216
I'm sorry. I can't use him.

19:47.887 --> 19:50.189
- Hey, Fonz.
- Yeah?

19:50.189 --> 19:53.826
How come you didn't just,
uh, send this heap

19:53.826 --> 19:55.695
over to the-the wrecking yard?

19:55.695 --> 19:57.997
I didn'tjunk it
for two reasons:

19:57.997 --> 20:01.300
one, the pay might make
tune-up history, (chuckles)

20:01.300 --> 20:03.369
and two, it was a challenge.

20:03.369 --> 20:06.305
I climbed the peak in Motorland.

20:06.305 --> 20:09.108
I think most guys would have
just left it to rot.

20:09.108 --> 20:11.811
Most guys would have had to.

20:11.811 --> 20:13.880
Right.

20:13.880 --> 20:17.150
Don't you think Chachi deserves
the same kind of consideration?

20:17.150 --> 20:19.185
Richie, this is a car.

20:19.185 --> 20:22.855
It needs a new starter,
pistons, brakes, transmission,

20:22.855 --> 20:25.624
a little time,
a little attention.

20:25.625 --> 20:28.728
"Little time, little attention."

20:28.728 --> 20:31.164
I get your drift,
but it didn't work.

20:31.164 --> 20:33.199
Your trick didn't work.

20:33.199 --> 20:34.567
Bring him in, anyway.

20:34.567 --> 20:37.068
Oh, oh, great.
All right, thanks, Fonz.

20:37.069 --> 20:38.370
Just a second.

20:38.371 --> 20:40.006
Chachi! Hey, Chachi,
come on, come on!

20:40.006 --> 20:42.542
Hurry, hurry!

20:42.542 --> 20:45.111
Chachi, Fonz...

20:45.111 --> 20:48.915
why don't you two just, uh,
have a little chat, okay?

20:48.915 --> 20:51.885
Just converse a little bit,
all right?

20:55.822 --> 20:57.654
Hi.

21:04.163 --> 21:05.765
Nice weather we're having.

21:05.765 --> 21:07.995
It'll do.

21:12.638 --> 21:13.939
Well?

21:13.940 --> 21:15.208
I'm looking for a job.

21:15.208 --> 21:17.877
You ever work in
a garage before, Mr. Arcola?

21:17.877 --> 21:19.178
Briefly.

21:19.178 --> 21:21.981
Well, let me tell you something,
Mr. Arcola.

21:21.981 --> 21:24.016
You work in this garage,

21:24.016 --> 21:27.052
every employee has
certain requirements to fill.

21:27.053 --> 21:28.054
Like what?

21:28.054 --> 21:29.956
Like what? Like number one:

21:29.956 --> 21:31.756
employee must be in school.
No kick-outs.

21:31.757 --> 21:32.858
I am in school.

21:32.859 --> 21:34.459
You ain't
for the next two weeks.

21:34.460 --> 21:35.695
I'm back in school now!

21:35.695 --> 21:38.563
- Don't you yell at me.
- Sorry.

21:38.564 --> 21:40.666
I had a little talk
with the principal.

21:40.666 --> 21:42.501
He let me back in on trial.

21:42.501 --> 21:43.736
I sold myself.

21:43.736 --> 21:45.371
How many ties went with you?

21:45.371 --> 21:47.273
Oh, lots. I had a one-cent sale.

21:47.273 --> 21:48.374
He couldn't resist them.

21:48.374 --> 21:49.569
(laughs)

21:52.678 --> 21:55.114
Requirement number two:

21:55.114 --> 21:58.117
employee must apologize
to former employer

21:58.117 --> 22:00.052
for getting uppity.

22:00.052 --> 22:01.153
Uppity?

22:01.153 --> 22:04.657
That's right, uppity.

22:04.657 --> 22:07.293
All right, uppity.

22:07.293 --> 22:10.963
Tell my former employer
I'm sorry I got uppity

22:10.963 --> 22:14.266
and it won't happen
no more, okay?

22:14.267 --> 22:15.867
- Okay.
- Do I get the job?

22:15.868 --> 22:18.704
I don't know.

22:18.704 --> 22:21.473
Now, look, Chach, I don't think
it's gonna work out, you know?

22:21.474 --> 22:25.342
You remind me too much
of myself when I was your age.

22:28.214 --> 22:30.049
On the other hand, look at me.

22:30.049 --> 22:31.813
I turned out perfect-amundo.

22:38.858 --> 22:42.228
Hmm.

22:42.228 --> 22:45.965
All right, we'll give it
one more shot.

22:45.965 --> 22:47.700
Ah, that's great, Fonz!

22:47.700 --> 22:48.701
That's great! Thanks!

22:48.701 --> 22:50.303
What do you want me to do?

22:50.303 --> 22:52.238
I want you to clean my office.

22:52.238 --> 22:54.340
Clean the office. Oh, sure.

22:54.340 --> 22:56.542
First thing in the morning.

22:56.542 --> 23:00.046
But first I want to go see
Cindy Turtleback.

23:00.046 --> 23:02.715
Wah-wah-wah.

23:02.715 --> 23:04.183
(Snaps fingers)

23:04.183 --> 23:05.384
Yeah, Fonz?

23:05.384 --> 23:09.655
There's a time for work
and a time for wah-wah.

23:09.655 --> 23:11.323
And with work,
comes responsibility.

23:11.324 --> 23:12.458
You get my drift?

23:12.458 --> 23:13.693
Yeah, I guess you're right.

23:13.693 --> 23:14.759
- Don't guess.
- You're right.

23:14.760 --> 23:15.961
That's right.

23:15.962 --> 23:18.431
I want you to put this
in your back pocket.

23:18.431 --> 23:19.565
Look like a mechanic.

23:19.565 --> 23:21.467
Thanks, Fonz.

23:21.467 --> 23:23.102
- Mm-hmm.
- Clean the office.

23:23.102 --> 23:24.170
That's right.

23:24.170 --> 23:25.770
I'll start with the calendar.

23:25.771 --> 23:28.907
I can't wait to do
Miss Carburetor.

23:28.908 --> 23:31.275
Keep your eyes off
that calendar!

23:33.512 --> 23:37.082
♪ La, la, la, la,
la, la, la ♪

23:37.083 --> 23:41.042
♪ La-la-la, la-la-la, la. ♪

23:45.758 --> 23:48.294
So, how'd you do
on the chemistry test, Rich?

23:48.294 --> 23:50.161
- Got a B-plus.
- Figures.

23:50.162 --> 23:51.789
How'd you do, Potsie?

23:52.832 --> 23:55.034
The guy's got it in for me.

23:55.034 --> 23:59.005
The guy's got it in for you?
(chuckles)

23:59.005 --> 24:01.606
Potsie, you blew up
the man's lab.

24:01.607 --> 24:04.877
It was only half a table.

24:04.877 --> 24:06.971
Besides, his eyebrows
will grow back.

24:08.981 --> 24:11.550
Come on, Malph. We got to go
pick up those blind dates.

24:11.550 --> 24:13.385
Oh, yeah.
Pots, wear your tie.

24:13.386 --> 24:15.955
I told the girls
we were roving ambassadors.

24:15.955 --> 24:18.549
- What country's Roving?
- No.

24:20.593 --> 24:21.761
Fun-loving guys.

24:21.761 --> 24:23.991
Yeah, they're nice.
(chuckles)

24:25.464 --> 24:27.023
(sighs):
Ah, Richie...

24:28.501 --> 24:31.095
Ever tell you about
Rosa Coletti?

24:32.238 --> 24:33.406
Yeah.

24:33.406 --> 24:36.442
I first met Rosa in '34.

24:36.442 --> 24:37.675
Or was it '35?

24:37.676 --> 24:38.911
'35, Al.

24:38.911 --> 24:41.247
That's right.
I'll never forget her.

24:41.247 --> 24:42.648
Neither will I.

24:42.648 --> 24:45.117
She was a-a tiny girl.

24:46.152 --> 24:48.988
BOTH:
Shiny black hair...

24:48.988 --> 24:50.855
big brown eyes...

24:50.856 --> 24:54.026
red lips...

24:54.026 --> 24:55.661
(both sigh)

